Terraform Commands:
    terraform init - Initializes the working directory by downloading required providers and modules and configuring the backend.
    terraform plan - Creates and shows an execution plan describing the actions Terraform will take to reach the desired state.
    terraform validate - Checks the configuration for syntax and internal consistency without contacting remote services.
    terraform apply [or] terraform apply -auto-approve - Applies the proposed changes to create, update, or delete infrastructure (use `-auto-approve` to skip the confirmation prompt).
    terraform destroy [or] terraform destroy -auto-approve - Destroys all managed infrastructure defined in the configuration (use `-auto-approve` to skip the confirmation prompt).

AWS Setup:
    create iam user - Create an IAM user and attach `AdministratorAccess`.
    install aws cli v2 - Install AWS CLI v2 on Windows (e.g. `winget install Amazon.AWSCLI`) and verify with `aws --version`.
    aws configure - Configure the CLI with Access Key ID, Secret Access Key, default region and output format.